<item>
            <title>[LU-18242] allow &apos;lfs df -m/-o&apos; to specify one MDT/OST</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18242</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As an extension to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17516&quot; title=&quot;add &amp;#39;lfs df --mdt&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;lfs df --ost&amp;#39; options&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17516&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17516&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; it would be useful if &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs df &amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt/&amp;#45;&amp;#45;ost&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; took an optional argument &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;INDEX&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to specify a single MDT/OST index for which to print the usage.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That would avoid a lot of cases where &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs df | grep ...&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is used in test scripts to find space usage for a particular target, and is likely equally useful for end users.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
